libcarvpath
------------------------------------------
LibCarvpath is a library for computer forensics carving tools.It provides the
low level needs of zero-storage carving using virtual paths. These virtual
file paths can be used in conjunction with the CarvFS filesystem.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libcarvpath-devel-2.3.0-1bl3
  libcarvpath2-2.3.0-1bl3
  libsqlite3_0-3.49.1-1
  libssl1.0-1.0.2u+za-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  libssl1.0-devel-1.0.2u+za-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/DNPA/libcarvpath

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/DNPA/libcarvpath/archive/refs/tags/R2.3.0rc8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libcarvpath-2.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libcarvpath-2.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libcarvpath-2.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcarvpath-2.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcarvpath2-2.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcarvpath-devel-2.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libcarvpath)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libcarvpath.README
  /usr/share/doc/libcarvpath/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libcarvpath/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libcarvpath/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libcarvpath/README

(libcarvpath2)
  /usr/bin/cygcarvpath-2.dll

(libcarvpath-devel)
  /usr/include/libcarvpath.h
  /usr/lib/libcarvpath.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libcarvpath.pc

